-- ── Branch ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Branch (branch.io), legally Branch Metrics, Inc., is a mobile measurement partner (MMP) and deep-linking platform founded in April 2014 in Palo Alto, California, by Alex Austin, Mike Molinet, Mada Seghete, and Dmitri Gaskin. It is not affiliated with Branch Insurance, Branch Furniture, or Branch Messenger - it is specifically the mobile attribution and linking company used across app marketing stacks. Branch's deep links route users from ads, email, SMS, social, and the mobile web directly into the right in-app screen, handling thousands of device and platform edge cases so links don't break across iOS, Android, and app-not-installed states. On top of linking, Branch provides privacy-safe, cross-channel attribution that ties ad spend and organic activity to in-app outcomes, unifying paid, owned, and organic performance data across more than 80 partner integrations, including Meta, Google, TikTok, Snap, Amplitude, and Braze. The platform reports serving mobile measurement and linking for over 100,000 apps and roughly 3.5 billion users worldwide, and it holds ISO 27001 certification. Branch has raised roughly 666 million dollars in venture funding, including a 300 million dollar Series F in February 2022 led by New Enterprise Associates that valued the company at 4 billion dollars, with additional backing from Founders Fund, Playground Global, and Pear VC.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Tiered subscription with custom, contact-sales pricing that is not fully published$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free trial available; paid plans are custom-quoted through Branch's sales team$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2014, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Mid-to-large company, several hundred employees estimated; exact current headcount not independently confirmed$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Palo Alto, California, USA (some corporate records also list a Redwood City, CA office)$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Branch.io Review: Mobile Deep Linking and Attribution Platform$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Branch (Branch.io) is a leading mobile measurement and deep linking platform. See how it works, its pricing tiers, and how it differs from Branch Insurance or Branch Furniture.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Branch, commonly known by its URL branch.io and legally registered as Branch Metrics, Inc., is one of the best-known names in mobile marketing infrastructure, alongside competitors like AppsFlyer and Adjust. It's worth flagging up front that 'Branch' is used by several unrelated companies - Branch Insurance, Branch Furniture, and Branch Messenger are all different businesses - and this profile is specifically about Branch Metrics, the mobile measurement and deep-linking company. Branch was founded in April 2014 by Alex Austin, Mike Molinet, Mada Seghete, and Dmitri Gaskin, reportedly after the founders ran into the problem of broken and unreliable app links while building their own product. The company's foundational technology is deep linking: instead of a marketing link simply opening an app to its home screen (or failing entirely if the app isn't installed), Branch's links route users to the exact in-app content that matches what they clicked, whether that click came from an email, an SMS, a social post, a paid ad, or the mobile web. Branch describes handling more than 6,000 device, platform, and install-state edge cases so that these deep links behave consistently across iOS, Android, and scenarios where the app isn't yet installed (deferred deep linking), which is a much harder engineering problem than it sounds given the fragmentation of mobile operating systems, browsers, and app stores. On top of linking, Branch operates as a full mobile measurement partner (MMP), providing attribution that connects marketing spend and organic activity to in-app outcomes across more than 80 integrated partners, including major ad platforms like Meta, Google, TikTok, and Snap, as well as analytics and engagement tools like Amplitude and Braze. Branch markets this as privacy-safe measurement, an important positioning given how significantly Apple's App Tracking Transparency and the shift toward SKAdNetwork (SKAN) have changed what attribution data is available on iOS; Branch's product lineup includes advanced SKAN modeling as part of its higher-tier offerings. The company reports scale metrics of over 100,000 customer apps and roughly 3.5 billion users measured worldwide, and holds ISO 27001 certification, which matters for enterprise buyers evaluating data-handling practices. Branch's pricing is structured around three named tiers - Basics, Essentials, and Enterprise - with capabilities like multi-touch attribution and unlimited partner connections unlocked in Essentials, and CTV/OTT attribution, LTV prediction, advanced SKAN modeling, and unlimited API access reserved for Enterprise. However, Branch does not publish specific list prices on its website; pricing is quoted through a sales process, and third-party sources describing real-world costs vary widely, from smaller reported starting figures up to tens of thousands of dollars annually for mid-market apps and well into six figures annually for the largest enterprise deployments with high monthly active user counts. Branch has raised substantial venture funding over its history - approximately 666 million dollars in total, including a 300 million dollar Series F round in February 2022 led by New Enterprise Associates that valued the company at 4 billion dollars, with additional investors including Founders Fund, Playground Global, and Pear VC - reflecting its position as one of the largest independent players in mobile attribution and linking.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'e431b41f-c262-4a08-8527-8e08946e3c29';

